 illustrations, This Is Our Life details the remarkable story of the Haida Project. A fascinating look at the meaning behind objects, the value of repatriation, and the impact of historical trajectories like colonialism, this is also a tender story of the understanding that grew between the Haida visitors and museum staff. Beautifully written and illustrated, This Is Our Life offers a compelling view of the transformative potential of a conversation hundreds of years in the making.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aCultural propertyxRepatriationzGreat Britain. 0aHaida Indians -- Museums. 0aHaida IndiansxMaterial culture. 0aHaida IndiansxMuseums. 0aMuseum techniqueszGreat Britain. 0aMuseums and IndianszGreat Britain. 0aMuseums and Indians. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Ethnic Studies / Native American Studies.2bisacsh1 aGladstone-Davies, Ruth, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPeers, Laura, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 athe Haida Repatriation Committee and staff of the Pitt Rivers Museum and British Museum, , eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2013z978311127412608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2013z978311127715808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of British Columbia eBook-Package 2013-2000z978311141860540uhttps://doi.org/10.59962/978077482542940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780774825429423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780774825429/original  a978-3-11-127412-6  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2013b2013  a978-3-11-127715-8  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2013b2013  a978-3-11-141860-5  University of British Columbia eBook-Package 2013-2000c2013d2